Q3. What is an operating system and give examples. Also, discuss its main functions
and responsibility (at least 6).
Ans:
It is an interface between a computer user and computer hardware.
it is a software which performs all the tasks like file management, memory management,
process management ,handling input and output and controll perpheral devices like pen drives,
printer, pentablet etc.

some os are Linux os, windows ,IOS;

Important function:

1.memory management:

It keeps tracks of primary memory, which parts of it is in use by whom and
in multiprogramming, the OS decides which process will get memory when and how
much and
allocates and de-allocates the memory when a process is terminated.


2.Device Management

It manages communication by their respective drivers.
it keeps track of all devices and decides which process gets the device when and for how much time;
allocates and de-allocates the devices in efficient way.

3.Security

By username and password ,it prevents unauthorized access to programs and data.

4.Control over system performance

Its records the time dalays b/w request for a service and response from a system.

5.Processor Management

In it ,OS decides which process gets the processor when and for how much time
It Keeps tracks of processor and status of process.
allocates and de-allocates the processes in efficient way.

6.File Management

It is organized into directories for easy navigation and usage.

it keeps track of information, location, uses, status .
Decides who gets the resources.
allocates and de-allocates the resources.